  "prompt": "What are the some of the best lines in English songs?",
  "response": "There are countless memorable lines in English songs that resonate with listeners for their poetic quality, emotional depth, or relatable themes. Here are some examples:\n\n1. **\"And in the end, the love you take is equal to the love you make.\"** - The Beatles, \"The End\"\n\n2. **\"You may say I'm a dreamer, but I'm not the only one.\"** - John Lennon, \"Imagine\"\n\n3. **\"It's something unpredictable, but in the end, it's right. I hope you had the time of your life.\"** - Green Day, \"Good Riddance (Time of Your Life)\"\n\n4. **\"Is it too late now to say sorry?\"** - Justin Bieber, \"Sorry\"\n\n5. **\"I will always love you.\"** - Whitney Houston, \"I Will Always Love You\"\n\n6. **\"Don't stop believin', hold on to that feelin'.\"** - Journey, \"Don't Stop Believin'\"\n\n7. **\"We don't need no education. We don't need no thought control.\"** - Pink Floyd, \"Another Brick in the Wall, Part 2\"\n\n8. **\"Cause you make me feel like I\u2019m living a teenage dream.\"** - Katy Perry, \"Teenage Dream\"\n\n9. **\"Hello from the other side, I must have called a thousand times.\"** - Adele, \"Hello\"\n\n10. **\"I wanna hold your hand.\"** - The Beatles, \"I Want to Hold Your Hand\"\n\nThese lines capture a wide range of emotions, from love and nostalgia to rebellion and hope, showing the power of music to convey deep feelings and thoughts.",
